[[File:CoruscantLivestockExchangeAndExhibition-WOSW.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The Coruscant Livestock Exchange and Exhibition]]
The '''Coruscant Livestock Exchange and Exhibition''' was held every [[Standard year/Legends|year]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and was the largest livestock fair in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. It was held in the stables, corrals, and halls of the [[Grand Symposium]]. The exhibition was a major event for animal dealers and [[Merchant/Legends|traders]] of all sorts. Many transactions, legal or otherwise, were held amidst the competitions, auctions and revelry. The Livestock exhibition gave many different beings an opportunity to learn more about one another and their various [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] through the exotic creatures they brought with them.

Amongst the animals in the outdoor exhibits were [[Ronto/Legends|rontos]], [[Kybuck/Legends|kybucks]], [[Bantha/Legends|banthas]], and [[Eopie/Legends|eopies]]. Avians included [[Nuna/Legends|nunas]], [[Urusai/Legends|urusais]], [[Pylat bird/Legends|pylat]] birds, and [[Neekoflight/Legends|neekoflight]]. [[Orbalisk]]s, [[Droch/Legends|droch]], and [[energy spider]]s were among some of the arthropods present. Amongst the Small Animal Hall were such creatures as [[chitlik]]s, [[Gizka/Legends|gizkas]], [[twirrl]]s, and [[Voorpak/Legends|voorpaks]]. [[Reek/Legends|Reeks]], [[Rancor/Legends|rancors]], [[Boar-wolf/Legends|boarwolves]], [[tusk cat]]s, and [[Nexu/Legends|nexu]] were all kept in an eerily lit area known as the Dangerous Animal level. [[Tauntaun/Legends|Tauntauns]], [[Jerba/Legends|jerbas]], [[Bursa/Legends|bursas]], [[Blurrg/Legends|blurrgs]], [[Fambaa/Legends|fambaas]], [[Falumpaset/Legends|falumpasets]], [[Kaadu/Legends|kaadu]], [[Shaak/Legends|shaaks]], [[Gualama/Legends|gualamas]], [[zeer]], [[Gundark/Legends|gundarks]], [[Ungulate|unidentified ungulates]] from [[Quermia/Legends|Quermia]], [[Horse/Legends|horses]], and [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamiri]] could be found as well.

This popular and well-attended event presented many opportunities for [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] and escape. Each [[Standard year/Legends|year]], unclaimed nunas ran about everywhere. Sometimes it was hard to tell which creatures were traders and which were livestock&mdash;at some point, some confused traders tried to purchase [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] traders present at the event.

The intense pollution on Coruscant claimed the lives of dozens of animals that were not used to the dirty air. The [[Thranta/Legends|thranta]], a highly sought-after beast at the [[Exchange]], was unable to handle the [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]], so used was it to the atmosphere of its natural habitat of [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], a planet that had a naturally clean atmosphere, and the [[Life Zone/Legends|life zone]] of [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]], where some were transplanted prior to Alderaan's [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destruction]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]]. [[Tendau Nandon]] and [[Dusque Mistflier]] went to one of the exhibitions prior to [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]].

In [[43 ABY|43.5 ABY]], a [[Skirmish at the Coruscant Livestock Exchange and Exhibition|skirmish]] broke out at the Livestock Exchange and Exhibition when the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Natua Wan]] fell prey to the [[Force psychosis|psychosis]] that was plaguing the [[New Jedi Order|Jedi Order]] while visiting the Exhibition with [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Solo]], their daughter [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], granddaughter [[Allana Djo Solo|Allana]], and fellow Knight [[Radd Minker]]. Wan freed many of the animals from the cages, hoping to cover her escape from the [[Grand Event Center]]. Organa Solo was forced to kill five boar-wolves in order to save a young boy who had fallen into their pen, and a mother nexu clamped down on an [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian's]] leg. Organa Solo stabbed the beast as the ramps stopped retracting. While pandemonium flooded the facility, Jaina Solo entered into a [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber duel]] with Wan, who was emptying a [[Bordok/Legends|bordok]] cage. Organa Solo and Minker soon arrived to assist Jaina, and Minker knocked Wan unconscious with a head-butt.

